\begin_layout Section*
Reasons For Proposing Changes
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The equation selected from Bolton (1980) is the less accurate of several
 alternatives presented there.
 Davies-Jones (2009) has pointed out that the form given as equation (39)
 in Bolton is more accurate, and Bolton also notes that.
 His more accurate formula is:
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
\Theta_{p}=\Theta_{DL}\exp\left\{ \left(\frac{3.036}{T_{L}}-0.00178\right)r\left(1+0.448\times10^{-3}r\right)\right\} \label{eq:Bolton39}\end{equation}

\end_inset

where
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
\Theta_{DL}=T_{k}\left(\frac{1000}{p_{d}}\right)^{0.2854}\left(\frac{T_{K}}{T_{L}}\right)^{0.28\times10^{-3}r}\label{eq:ThetaDL}\end{equation}

\end_inset

is the potential temperature of dry air at the lifting condensation level
 (LCL) and 
\begin_inset Formula $T_{L}$
\end_inset

 is the temperature at the LCL as given by (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:Bolton21"

\end_inset

).
 Equation (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:Bolton39"

\end_inset

 takes into account the effect of humidity on the ratio of specific heats
 of the water-saturated air parcel.
 This form appears to be a better choice than the one now in use.
\begin_inset Foot
status open

